Here's a JavaScript function that takes an array of 5 numbers as its input and checks if any of them are prime numbers, if they are, prints the first number. Here's the function:

```js
function isPrime(arr) {
    for (let i = 2; i <= arr.length; i++) {
        for (let j = 2; j <= arr[i-1]; j++) {
            if (arr[i] % j === 0) {
                return false;
            }
        }
    }
    return arr[0] % arr[0] === 0 ? false : true;
}
```

